# Semgrep ignore — upstream Google Online Boutique demo source
#
# All code under src/ is the unmodified Google microservices-demo application
# (https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/microservices-demo). Semgrep correctly
# identifies real security issues in that code (insecure gRPC, missing cookie
# flags, math/rand, HTTP without TLS, etc.) — these are intentional simplifications
# in the demo and are not production code written by this team.
#
# Excluding src/ keeps the SAST gate meaningful: it will still block on any
# security issues introduced in infrastructure code, workflow files, or scripts
# that this team owns. Trivy SCA continues to scan src/ for dependency CVEs
# independently of this file.
#
# If custom services are added to src/ by this team, remove the relevant
# directory from this ignore list so those files are scanned.
src/
